to the editor re future presidents stop here op ed march 7 by larry divney the genesis of office seeking politicians appearing on television comedy shows was richard m nixon 's guest appearance in 1968 on the hit television show laugh in nixon had no qualms in going on the program and showing that he had a sense of humor creating the classic moment when he deadpanned the show 's trademark quip sock it to me this rare and unexpectedly wonderful glimpse of nixon comedy helped in selling the deeply flawed candidate to the public phil hall new york march 7 2000

